formThreeBId.notesToCertificate:
1. The Certificate has been issued based on information and explanation given to us, books of accounts, Architect certificate, Engineer certificate and other records produced before us for verification by the management of company.
2. The Company has made reversal of GST Credit Claimed earlier in terms of the new provisions of GST law and accordingly the cost of construction / development claimed is higher compared to cost certified by engineer due to reversal/ ineligible GST Credit.
3.The project wise details of payments to vendor is not maintained in the books of accounts and we have relied on the payments adjusted against project payables as certified by the management.
4.The Indirect Expenses and Overheads has been apportioned in the Onsite Cost based on the development cost incurred till date in respect of each projects.
5.The Interest cost incurred for common borrowings has been apportioned in the Finance cost based on the development cost incurred till date in respect of each projects.
